'''Enchanted bolts''' are [[gem]]-tipped [[crossbow (weapon)|crossbow]] [[bolts]] enchanted through the [[Enchant Crossbow Bolt]] spell to obtain a secondary effect. All enchanted bolts can be traded, with the exception of [[enchanted jade bolts]].

While players can only add certain gem bolt tips to specific [[metal bolts]], [[dragon bolts]] can have any type of gem bolt tips added to them.

The enchanted bolt's effects are randomly triggered, and offer a variety of effects depending upon the type of gem tipped onto the bolts. The chance of the special effect occurring is increased by 10% upon the completion of the [[Hard Kandarin Diary]].

The [[Zaryte crossbow]] has a [[passive effect]] that will increase damage inflicted by bolt effects by 10% of damage inflicted. For example, with [[ruby bolts (e)|enchanted ruby bolts]], the bolt's special effect, ''Blood Forfeit'', would deal 22% of the opponent's current [[hitpoints]] with a cap of 110 damage, rather than the usual 20% damage and 100 hitpoint damage cap.

